The functional mushroom market is segmented by type, form, functionality, and distribution channel. In terms of type, the market includes popular varieties such as Reishi, Cordyceps, Lion's Mane, Chaga, and others. These different types offer various health benefits and are sought after by consumers looking to improve their well-being. The form of functional mushrooms can vary from fresh to dried to powdered, with each form offering convenience and versatility in consumption. Functionality plays a crucial role in the market as different mushrooms provide unique health benefits such as antioxidant properties, immune enhancement, anti-inflammatory effects, and boosting energy and stamina. Lastly, the distribution channels include online retail and offline retail, catering to the diverse preferences of consumers in accessing these products.

